column1: #text=Weekly grocery shopping begins at the local supermarket down the street .
#text=It 's the closest by with a great selection .
#text=It may not be the cheapest but nothing compares in how close it is .
#text=Once I am at the store , I usually head straight to the fruits and vegetable sections first .
#text=I will grab all the fruits and veggies that I think I will need for the week .
#text=I do n't really go with a shopping list or anything in mind .
#text=Usually whatever looks the freshest or is on sale is what I tend to buy .
#text=After selecting these items , I will move to the proteins .
#text=Sometimes it is chicken and sometimes it beef .
#text=It depends on the vegetables I 've just selected to determine which type of protein I will be purchasing .
#text=Lastly , once those are done I will pick up the packaged goods such as milk , bread , eggs , and cereal .
#text=I do n't each much junk food or processed foods so this is basically all I will get for a typical trip to the grocery store .
